sec.p:
To a 250 ml round-bottomed flask, 14.98 g (70 mmol) of 4-phenoxybenzoic acid, 50 ml of SOCl2, and 1 ml of DMF were added. The mixture was stirred at reflux temperature for 4 h. After the removal of SOCl2 under reduced pressure, the residue was dissolved in 180 ml of DMAc in the presence of  nitrogen, followed by the addition of 7.44 g (30 mmol) of 4,4′-diaminodiphenyl sulfone at 0°C by stirring. The reaction mixture was stirred at 0°C for 1 h at room temperature for 4 h, and poured into water (100 ml). The solid product obtained was filtered and washed with water and ethanol. The crude product was recrystallized from DMF/EtOH (VDMF/VEtOH = 1:2) and dried under vacuum at 100°C to obtain 15.74 g of white crystals. Yield 82%; mp 292–293°C; FTIR (KBr) ν (cm−1): 3386, 3067, 1665, 1588, 1504, 1400, 1323, 1243, 1152, 726; 
